==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sealer
<hw>Seal"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who seals;
especially, an officer whose duty it is to seal writs or instruments, to
stamp weights and measures, or the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sealer</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sealer
<hw>Sealer</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A mariner or a vessel engaged in the
business of capturing seals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sea letter</ent>⟦br⟧
